column4: A memory dump obtains the line: "CPU 0: Hot: hi: 0, btch: 1 usd: 0 Cold: hi:0, btch: 1 usd: 0" (http://ubuntuusers.de/paste/14722/). What do these abbreviations mean?
It does matter because I want to understand my Ubuntu and thus use it intelligently.
Thank you for hinting me at /proc/meminfo
